The Inspector General of Police Force has appointed a new Force Public Relations Officer, Force Headqarters, Abuja, CSP Olumuyiwa Adejobi, to takeover from CP Frank Mba. The Inspector-General of Police had nominated CP Mba for the Senior Executive Course at the National Institute for Policy and Strategic Studies (NIPSS), Kuru, Jos, Plateau State.
CP Mba handed over the Force Public Relations Department to CSP Olumuyiwa Adejobi, who was the DFPRO at the Police Headquarters, while Mba was the FPRO.
It was highlighted that Olumuyiwa Adejobi, a Chief Superintendent of Police, graduated from the prestigious University of Ibadan where he studied Archeology and Geography (Combined Honours). He also holds a Master’s degree in Peace and Conflict Studies from the University.
CSP Olumuyiwa Adejobi was Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO) of the Ogun State Police Command from 2008 – 2016; PPRO Zone 2 Headquarters, Onikan, Lagos, in 2016 and PPRO Lagos State Police Command between September 2020 and August 2021.
CSP Olumuyiwa is an experienced communicator and image manager who has achieved great strides in his previous appointments. He is a member of several professional bodies and associations which include the Nigerian Institute of Public Relations (NIPR); International Public Relations Association (IPRA); Pointman Leadership Institute, USA; International Association of Chiefs of Police (IACP), USA; and the Institute of Corporate Administration, Nigeria.
 
